<activity xml:id="act-PartialFractionCompare">
    <title>Comparing Rational Integrands</title>
    <task>
        <statement>
            <p>
                Try to integrate the following:
                <me>
                    \int \frac{9x+6}{x^2+3x-4}\;dx
                </me>.
                Explain what about this integral makes things very difficult.
            </p>
        </statement>
        <hint>
            <p>
                Annoyingly, you can write this as:
                <me>
                    \frac{9}{2}\int \frac{2x+3 - \frac{5}{3}}{x^2+3x-4}\;dx = \frac{9}{2}\int \frac{2x+3}{x^2+3x-4} \;dx - \frac{15}{2}\int \frac{1}{x^2+3x-4}\;dx
                </me>.
                Now explain why the second integral is difficult.
            </p>
        </hint>
    </task>
    <task>
        <statement>
            <p>
                Confirm that
                <me>
                    \frac{6}{x+4} + \frac{3}{x-1} = \frac{9x+6}{x^2+3x-4}
                </me>.
            </p>
        </statement>
    </task>
    <task>
        <statement>
            <p>
                Try to integrate the following:
                <me>
                    \int \frac{6}{x+4} + \frac{3}{x-1}\;dx
                </me>.
            </p>
        </statement>
    </task>
    <task>
        <statement>
            <p>
                Which integral of the two would you rather integrate? Why? 
            </p>
        </statement>
    </task>
    
</activity>